			<div class="button">	
				<%= image_tag 'icons/home-icon.png', { id: 'home' } %>
				<h2>Home</h2>
			</div>
		{{/link-to}}
		</div>
		
		<div class="link">
		{{#link-to "app.experience" activeClass="selected"}}
			<div class="button">	
				<%= image_tag 'icons/experience-icon.png', { id: 'experience' } %>
				<h2>Exp</h2>
			</div>
		{{/link-to}}
		</div>
		
		<div class="link">
		{{#link-to "app.skills"	activeClass="selected"}}
			<div class="button">	
				<%= image_tag 'icons/skills-icon.png', { id: 'skills' } %>
				<h2>Skills</h2>
			</div>
		{{/link-to}}
		</div>
		
		<div class="link">
		{{#link-to "app.references"	activeClass="selected"}}
			<div class="button">	
				<%= image_tag 'icons/references-icon.png', { id: 'references' } %>
				<h2>Ref</h2>
			</div>
		{{/link-to}}
		</div>
		
		<div class="link">
		{{#link-to "app.about" activeClass="selected"}}
			<div class="button">	
				<%= image_tag 'icons/about-icon.png', { id: 'about' } %>
				<h2>About</h2>
			</div>
		{{/link-to}}
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="section">
		{{outlet}}
	</div>

	<div id="app" class='footer'>
		<div id="baddies">Would you like bagels? <a onClick="start();">YES</a>/<a onClick="stop();">NO</a></div> |
		<div id="copyright">Â© MMXIV Steven J. Justin</div>
	</div>
	
</script>

<!-- App Child Templates -->

<script type="text/x-handlebars" data-template-name="app/index">
	<div id="index" class="content">
	</div>
</script>	

<script type="text/x-handlebars" data-template-name="app/references">	
	<div class="content">
		<div class="description">
			<div class="text">These are the poor saps I dooped into vouching for me.</div>
		</div>
		
		{{#each}}
		<div class="item">
			<div class="bold">{{name}}</div>
			<div>{{position}} at {{location}}</div>
			<div>{{phoneNumber}}</div>
			<div>{{emailAddress}}</div>
		</div>
		{{/each}}

		<div class="text">This is a personal site, you may not contact these people on my behalf. Their data is here as example content. If you are interested in contacting these people as my references please ask me and I will provide you with their completed information.</div>
	</div>
</script>

<script type="text/x-handlebars" data-template-name="app/about">
	<div id="about" class="content">
		
		<div class="photo">
			<img id='me' src="https://graph.facebook.com/nvts8a/picture?height=410">
			<%= image_tag "frame.png", { id: 'frame' } %> 
			<div id="loading">DON'T PANIC</div>
		</div>
		
		<h1 id="who" {{action "toggleSubsection" on="click"}}>WHO?</h1>
		
		<div class="subsection hidden" id="who">
			<div class="text">
				My name is Steven Justin, I was born and raised in metro Detroit. Currently I live in Chicago, IL. I've been working in software engineering since 2008 and web development since 2012. 
			</div>
			<br/>
			<div class="text">
				I'm a huge gamer, both video and board games, and a computer hardware enthusiast.
			</div>
			<br/>
			<div class="text">
				Below are some places you may feel free to contact me professionally.
			</div>

			<div id="social" class="sites">
				<a href="https://twitter.com/nvts8a" target="_blank">
					<%= image_tag "icons/twitter.png" %>
				</a>	
				<a href="https://github.com/nvts8a" target="_blank">
					<%= image_tag "icons/github.png" %>
				</a>
				<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=51585283" target="_blank">
					<%= image_tag "icons/linkedin.png" %>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>

		<h1 id="what" {{action "toggleSubsection" on="click"}}>WHAT?</h1>
	
		<div class="subsection hidden" id="what">
			<div class="text">
				The content is a personal blog built using the Blogger API as well as essentially my resume. It was the only content I could think ot that was:
				<ul id="self_indulgent_excuses">
					<li>Already generated</li>
					<li>Can continue to be generated</li>
					<li>In sections</li>
					<li>Needs to be ordered</li>
					<li>Pulls data via API calls</li>
					<li>Self indulgent</li>
				</ul>
				So that is what you get. A crazy looking, crazy implemented, blog-resume. But all of these guys helped me do it:	
			</div>
			
			<div id="credit" class="sites">
				<a href="http://emberjs.com/" target="_blank">
					<%= image_tag "icons/ember.png" %>
				</a>
				<a href="https://developers.google.com/blogger/" target="_blank">
					<%= image_tag "icons/blogger.png" %>
				</a>
				<a href="#" target="_blank">
					<%= image_tag "icons/temp.png" %>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<h1 id="where" {{action "toggleSubsection" on="click"}}>WHERE?</h1>
		
		<div class="subsection hidden" id="where">
			<div class="text">
				You can pull this entire website down from GitHub <a href="https://github.com/nvts8a/nvts8a/">here</a>.
			</div>
			<br/>
			<div class="text">
				Feel free to check out the source, learn from it, laugh at it, reuse it, or alter it.
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<h1 id="when" {{action "toggleSubsection" on="click"}}>WHEN?</h1>
		
		<div class="subsection hidden" id="when">
			<div class="text">
				I want to begin updating my blog every Monday and the site with new features I can, between work and other projects and hobbies, I get to it when I get to it.
			</div>
			<br/>
			<div class="text">
				I began creating the site in late 2013, so if you're from the future, I welcome you! But don't laugh if some of these technologies are out of date. You can view all changes to the webstie source <a href="https://github.com/nvts8a/nvts8a/commits/master">here</a>.
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<h1 id="why" {{action "toggleSubsection" on="click"}}>WHY?</h1>
		
		<div class="subsection hidden" id="why">
			<div class="text">
				This website is a personal project of mine. Working and being trained in backend development I lost touch in all the amazing things happening in the front end space and wanted a sandbox to play in.
				<br/>
				<br/>
			</div>
				
			<div class="text">
				So here it is. This site is a Frankenstein's monster of languages, technologies, and frameworks.
				<br/>
				<br/>
			</div>
			
			<div class="photo">
				<%= image_tag "frankenstein.png" %>
			</div>
				
			<div class="text">
				You might look at the source or the pull it down from Git and think: "WHY!? WHY!? Why would he use Ember for this? Why is his CSS crazy? Why are there flying bagels?" 
				The answer is, just because. Just because I didn't know how and I wanted to try and figure it out. 
				It might not always be the greatest way to do it or conforming to any best practices but I did it and you can deal with it.
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</script>	



